\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Three coordination regimes for ASR and MT sharing one GPU. The submitted system uses the strict ASR--MT alternation in\nobreakspace  {}(c). In full async mode\nobreakspace  {}(a), successive MT launches need not correspond to comparable source-time increments: a long MT decode can absorb several incoming ASR updates, while the next relaunch may cover much less newly available audio. That makes history-dependent policies such as local agreement \citep  {liu20s_interspeech} less natural to calibrate there than an attention-only policy such as AlignAtt, which scores each draft directly against the currently accessible source prefix.\relax }}{9}{figure.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:coord-regimes}{{7}{9}{Three coordination regimes for ASR and MT sharing one GPU. The submitted system uses the strict ASR--MT alternation in~(c). In full async mode~(a), successive MT launches need not correspond to comparable source-time increments: a long MT decode can absorb several incoming ASR updates, while the next relaunch may cover much less newly available audio. That makes history-dependent policies such as local agreement \citep {liu20s_interspeech} less natural to calibrate there than an attention-only policy such as AlignAtt, which scores each draft directly against the currently accessible source prefix.\relax }{figure.7}{}}
